Now that we've analyzed the numerical features, let's analyze the categorical ones and examine their relationship with the target variable.

In[9]:
# Count plot for a categorical feature (e.g., ProductType)
sns.countplot(x='ProductType', data=data, hue='EverDelinquent')
plt.title("Product Type vs EverDelinquent")
plt.show()

# Bar plot of the average delinquency rate by ProductType
product_type_delinquency = data.groupby('ProductType')['EverDelinquent'].mean().reset_index()
sns.barplot(x='ProductType', y='EverDelinquent', data=product_type_delinquency)
plt.title("Average Delinquency Rate by Product Type")
plt.show()

After that, we'll analyze the correlations between numerical features and the target varibales.

In[11]:
# Handle non-numeric values in the dataset
# Convert columns to numeric if appropriate, forcing errors to NaN (which can be handled)
data = data.apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='coerce')

# Now only the numeric columns will be included in the correlation matrix
numeric_data = data.select_dtypes(include=[float, int])

# Correlation matrix for all numeric features
corr_matrix = numeric_data.corr()

# Visualizing the correlation matrix
sns.heatmap(corr_matrix, annot=True, fmt='.2f', cmap='coolwarm')
plt.title("Correlation Matrix")
plt.show()

# Focus on the correlation of features with 'EverDelinquent'
if 'EverDelinquent' in corr_matrix.columns:
    corr_with_target = corr_matrix['EverDelinquent'].sort_values(ascending=False)
    print("Correlation with EverDelinquent:\n", corr_with_target)
else:
    print("'EverDelinquent' is not in the numeric columns.")

Summary and Insights

  • The dataset contains some missing values, particularly in certain columns.
  • The target variable EverDelinquent is imbalanced, with a higher proportion of non-delinquent loans.
  • Some numeric features, such as CreditScore and DTI, show interesting distributions and relationships with the target variable.
  • There are strong correlations between certain features that could be further explored during preprocessing.
  • Categorical features like ProductType also show different delinquency rates, indicating potential predictive power.
